01:01.271 --> 01:05.108
and it happened
in the 1932 World Series.

01:05.191 --> 01:08.653
The story goes that in the bottom
of the ninth inning with two outs,

01:08.778 --> 01:11.448
a full count
and the tying run on base,

01:11.531 --> 01:14.784
Babe Ruth raised his arm and pointed
to the center field bleachers.

01:14.868 --> 01:19.372
No one believed it,
because nobody had ever done it before.

01:19.497 --> 01:22.208
But The Babe
was calling his shot.

01:22.334 --> 01:28.173
On the next pitch, the Great Bambino
hit a towering 400-foot home run.

01:28.298 --> 01:31.217
And even although he'd been
a hero before that,

01:31.343 --> 01:34.429
that's pretty much
how he became a legend.

01:34.512 --> 01:38.683
Thirty years later, a kid named
Benjamin Franklin Rodriguez...

01:38.808 --> 01:40.810
became a neighborhood legend.

01:40.935 --> 01:43.104
It was in the greatest summer
of my life...

01:43.188 --> 01:45.106
when he taught me
to play baseball,

01:45.190 --> 01:47.400
and he became my best friend.

01:47.525 --> 01:51.196
And he got me out of the biggest
pickle I'd ever be in.

02:21.059 --> 02:23.687
Go! Go! Go!

03:02.475 --> 03:05.562
Come over at 9:00.

03:05.645 --> 03:07.564
All right.
See you later.

03:13.737 --> 03:17.115
I moved to the neighborhood
two weeks before school let out.

03:17.198 --> 03:18.491
It was the same summer
that Dodger Maury Wills would
break the stolen bases record.

03:18.491 --> 03:21.995
It was the same summer
that Dodger Maury Wills would
break the stolen bases record.

03:22.120 --> 03:24.205
So with something
that incredible going on,

03:24.289 --> 03:28.418
it should've started off with loads
of great things happening for me,

03:28.501 --> 03:30.545
but it didn't.

03:30.629 --> 03:35.008
I was from another state,
and I didn't have a single
friend in a thousand miles.

03:36.301 --> 03:38.720
It was a lousy way
to end up the fifth grade,

03:38.803 --> 03:41.931
'cause I had zip time
to make friends before summer.

03:42.015 --> 03:45.935
And that's about
where it all started.

03:50.148 --> 03:53.401
My real dad died
when I was just a little kid.

03:53.485 --> 03:57.947
My mom had married Bill about a year
before we moved to the Valley.

03:58.031 --> 04:02.994
At the time, he and I were still
getting used to each other.

04:03.119 --> 04:05.789
Yeah.

04:07.624 --> 04:10.752
- Um, Dad?
- Mm-hm m?

04:10.835 --> 04:12.754
I -I mean Bill.

04:12.837 --> 04:17.759
- Remember you-- you promised
you'd teach me to play catch?
- Mm-hmm.

04:17.841 --> 04:20.053
Um,

04:20.178 --> 04:22.096
w-well,
could you teach me?

04:23.264 --> 04:25.809
Yeah. Sure.

04:32.023 --> 04:33.900
Okay.

04:34.025 --> 04:36.236
- Okay?
- Thanks.

04:42.033 --> 04:43.910
Sorry.

05:25.785 --> 05:29.080
I'd followed them
to the sandlot once after school.

05:29.164 --> 05:31.708
I'd never seen any place like it.

05:31.833 --> 05:34.836
It was like their own little
baseball kingdom or something.

05:34.919 --> 05:37.797
It was the greatest place
I'd ever seen anyway.

05:37.922 --> 05:39.883
- Bertram.
- But they were good,

05:39.966 --> 05:41.885
- real good.
- Come on, Bertram!

05:41.968 --> 05:44.804
And all I had was a plastic toy mitt
that my grandmother gave me...

05:44.929 --> 05:47.307
for my birthday when I was six.

05:47.432 --> 05:51.645
But when I finally got up enough guts to
go out there and try and make friends,

05:51.770 --> 05:55.357
I found out that they never kept score,
they never chose sides,

05:55.440 --> 05:57.734
they never even really
stopped playing the game.

05:57.817 --> 06:02.322
It just went on forever.
Every day they picked up where
they left off the day before.

06:02.447 --> 06:05.450
- It was like an endless dream game.
- Come on! Come on!

06:05.575 --> 06:08.578
There was only eight of them,
so they didn't have a whole team.

06:08.662 --> 06:12.582
So even though I didn't know
how to play, I figured
I could be the ninth man...

06:12.666 --> 06:15.835
and maybe just stand in the outfield
somewhere and take up space.

06:15.960 --> 06:19.714
- Squints!
- Of course, if I'd have known what was
gonna happen when I got there,

06:19.798 --> 06:24.302
- I got it!
- I probably never would've gone.

06:24.427 --> 06:26.096
- Nice catch.
- Yeah.

06:32.268 --> 06:36.398
Come on!

06:54.833 --> 06:57.836
Come on, Benny,
hit a homer!

06:57.919 --> 06:59.838
- Come on!
- Hey, batter, batter, batter!

06:59.963 --> 07:02.173
- Whoa!
- Watch out!

07:22.861 --> 07:25.447
Okay, I'll get it!
Get it.

07:25.530 --> 07:29.826
Don't be a goofus. Don't be a goofus!
Don't be a goofus!

07:38.376 --> 07:42.672
- Throw the ball back! Come on!
- Yeah, hurry up!

07:53.516 --> 07:55.685
We are waiting!

07:55.769 --> 07:57.729
Come on! Throw it!

08:02.942 --> 08:06.655
- Come on, toss me the ball!
- Come on!

08:06.738 --> 08:08.698
Come on!

08:14.287 --> 08:18.792
Oh, my God!

08:20.543 --> 08:22.545
My life's over.

08:22.629 --> 08:25.131
Did you see that hand?

08:28.760 --> 08:30.679
If it wasn't for Benny,

08:30.762 --> 08:33.431
I never would've made
a single friend that summer,

08:33.556 --> 08:36.101
'cause all the rest of those
guys thought I was a lost cause.

08:37.477 --> 08:40.020
Even before we became friends,

08:40.105 --> 08:44.567
Benny and me were connected, connected
for the one moment later that summer...

08:44.651 --> 08:46.695
when I'd get us all
into the biggest pickle...

08:46.778 --> 08:49.572
any of us had ever seen.

08:57.247 --> 08:59.791
Night, hon.

08:59.916 --> 09:03.420
Oh, I'm sorry, Mom.
It was an accident.

09:12.762 --> 09:16.016
Scotty, have you made
any friends yet?

09:17.642 --> 09:20.061
- No.
- Why not, honey?

09:22.147 --> 09:24.149
'Cause I'm still new.

09:24.274 --> 09:28.528
I don't want you sitting around in here
all summer fiddling with this stuff...

09:28.653 --> 09:30.655
like you did last summer
and the one before.

09:30.780 --> 09:33.283
I know you're smart,
and I'm proud of you.

09:33.366 --> 09:37.912
I want you to get out into the fresh air
and make some friends.

09:37.996 --> 09:41.458
Run around,
scrape your knees, get dirty.

09:41.541 --> 09:43.460
Climb trees, hop fences.

09:43.543 --> 09:46.796
Get into trouble,
for crying out loud.

09:46.880 --> 09:49.883
Not too much, but some.
You have my permission.

09:50.008 --> 09:53.470
How many mothers do you know who
say something like that to their sons?

09:53.553 --> 09:56.264
Well, none mothers, I guess.

09:56.348 --> 10:01.019
Honey, I want you to make
some friends this summer. Lots of them.

10:02.145 --> 10:04.105
Yeah, I know.

10:04.189 --> 10:06.107
But I'm not good
at anything, Mom.

10:06.191 --> 10:08.109
Face it,
I'm just an egghead.

10:08.193 --> 10:12.656
Honey, you'll always be just an egghead
with an attitude like that.

10:29.172 --> 10:31.383
Well?

10:33.093 --> 10:35.428
Well?

10:35.553 --> 10:39.224
- He's too busy, Mom.
- Oh, no, honey, he's not.
He has some time.

10:39.349 --> 10:42.435
You go on back out there
and ask him.

10:44.562 --> 10:46.648
- Uh, Bill, uh--
- Yeah?

10:46.731 --> 10:49.943
I mean, Dad, uh, can we--

10:50.068 --> 10:54.406
I mean, could you, like you said,
teach me to play catch?

10:54.531 --> 10:56.866
Yeah. Sure.

10:56.950 --> 10:58.868
But I gotta get
this done, okay?

10:58.952 --> 11:01.454
- Okay, thanks.
- All right.

11:01.579 --> 11:03.415
- Bill?
- Yeah?

11:03.540 --> 11:07.127
Uh, couldn't you take a break
and teach him now?

11:07.252 --> 11:09.587
- Mom, it's okay, really.
- Honey,

11:09.713 --> 11:12.132
I said I would, and I will,
but I'm under the gun here.

11:12.257 --> 11:14.467
How long could it take?

11:14.592 --> 11:16.970
Can't you spare half an hour
and show him now?

11:17.095 --> 11:19.597
- Mom, really, it's okay.
- All right.

11:21.349 --> 11:24.019
Okay. I'll get my glove.

11:27.272 --> 11:30.859
See? I told you.

11:30.942 --> 11:33.153
Oh, great.

11:33.278 --> 11:35.697
All right, Scotty, get down
to that end of the yard.

11:35.780 --> 11:37.365
Okay.

11:37.449 --> 11:40.118
Now, the key to this game
is keeping your eye on the ball.

11:40.243 --> 11:43.788
No matter whether you're in the field
or at bat, eye on the ball, okay?

11:43.913 --> 11:45.957
All right. Uh, yeah.
I think so.

11:46.082 --> 11:48.543
Where the ball goes,
your glove should go. Got it?

11:48.626 --> 11:50.462
Okay.

11:50.587 --> 11:52.422
Okay. All right.

11:56.384 --> 11:58.845
Darn. Sorry.

11:58.970 --> 12:00.764
It's all right.
All right.

12:09.064 --> 12:11.608
Um-- Uh, here.

12:14.194 --> 12:16.112
Okay.

12:16.196 --> 12:18.281
Okay, I'm ready.

12:18.365 --> 12:22.118
Eye on the ball, okay?
Got it?

12:22.202 --> 12:23.453
Okay.

12:23.536 --> 12:26.289
If the ball moves,
move your glove. Got it?

12:26.373 --> 12:27.791
Yeah.

12:27.874 --> 12:30.293
All right. Here we go.

12:35.632 --> 12:38.385
Okay. You just need a bigger glove.
Throw it back to me this time.

12:41.137 --> 12:43.014
Throw it back.

12:58.446 --> 13:01.533
Okay. Scotty,
keep your eye on the ball.

13:01.658 --> 13:03.994
Okay. Got it.

13:04.077 --> 13:05.328
Okay.

13:06.830 --> 13:09.207
Ow! Oh, my eye!

13:09.332 --> 13:12.460
Ow! Ow! Oh!

13:12.544 --> 13:14.462
Ow! Ow!

13:14.546 --> 13:17.757
- What happened?
- My eye.

13:17.882 --> 13:20.844
- Honey, get some ice. Ice.
- No, I got it.

13:20.969 --> 13:22.887
- Here you go.
- Those were for dinner.

13:22.971 --> 13:24.889
- Oh!
- Just hold it up there.

13:24.973 --> 13:26.891
Nice and hard.
Press it against-- Yeah.

13:26.975 --> 13:29.811
- I just took my eye off the ball, Mom.
- Yeah, but you caught it.

13:29.894 --> 13:32.605
Just keep that on for, like, an hour.

13:32.731 --> 13:35.608
It'll still be black,
but it won't swell.

13:35.734 --> 13:38.194
Sorry.

13:38.320 --> 13:40.572
Gotta watch out
for that curve.

13:47.537 --> 13:49.414
Hey.

13:52.292 --> 13:55.420
I'm gonna play some ball.
We need an extra guy. You wanna go?

13:55.545 --> 13:59.007
- No. Thanks.
- Why not? Don't you like baseball?

13:59.090 --> 14:01.509
- Oh, yeah, but--
- But what?

14:03.970 --> 14:06.723
But my glove--
it's busted.

14:06.806 --> 14:11.186
Uh, see? Now I can't go.
Thanks, though.

14:11.269 --> 14:13.104
It's okay.

14:14.272 --> 14:16.149
I got an extra one.

14:18.318 --> 14:20.278
Come on. Let's go.

14:23.114 --> 14:25.492
Mom, I'm gonna go
play some ball!

14:25.617 --> 14:27.494
I'll be back
in a little while.

14:27.619 --> 14:29.496
Come on. Let's go.

14:32.457 --> 14:35.377
And I'm Babe Ruth.

14:42.884 --> 14:45.470
Listen. Ready?

14:45.595 --> 14:48.139
Check this out.

14:48.264 --> 14:50.558
I'm the Great Bambino.

14:50.642 --> 14:52.769
What?

14:52.894 --> 14:55.897
- I'm the Great Bambino.
- What?

14:55.981 --> 14:58.191
I'm the Great Bambino.

14:58.316 --> 15:00.276
Oh!

15:00.360 --> 15:02.195
Who's that?

15:06.199 --> 15:08.118
What?

15:08.201 --> 15:11.121
I had no idea
who they were talking about.

15:11.204 --> 15:14.833
- What did he say?
- What, were you born in a barn, man?

15:14.958 --> 15:16.835
Yeah, what planet
are you from?

15:16.960 --> 15:19.254
But there was
no way I could let them know.

15:19.337 --> 15:21.548
You never heard
of the Sultan of Swat?

15:21.673 --> 15:23.591
The Titan of Terror?

15:23.675 --> 15:26.803
- The Colossus of Clout?
- The Colossus of Clout!

15:26.886 --> 15:30.515
- The King of Crash, man.
- So I lied.

15:30.640 --> 15:34.019
Oh, yeah, the Great Bambino.
Of course.

15:34.144 --> 15:36.021
I thought you said,
"the Great Bambi."

15:36.146 --> 15:38.273
That wimpy deer?

15:38.356 --> 15:41.735
Yeah. I guess. Sorry.

15:44.487 --> 15:49.868
Anyway, Scott, that's
Timmy and Tommy Timmons,

15:49.993 --> 15:52.454
Mike "Squints" Palledorous,

15:52.537 --> 15:55.040
Alan McClellan--
we call him Yeah-Yeah--

15:55.123 --> 15:57.709
Bertram Grover Weeks,

15:57.834 --> 16:00.295
Kenny DeNunez
and Hamilton Porter.

16:00.378 --> 16:02.839
We call him Ham.
Guys, this is Scott Smalls.

16:02.922 --> 16:04.841
Hi.

16:06.718 --> 16:10.555
Yeah, um, wel I, he's gonna play with us
'cause he makes nine.

16:10.639 --> 16:13.933
Now we've got a whole team. We're
wasting time. Let's go to the sandlot.

16:14.059 --> 16:16.853
- Benny, it's 9:00 in the morning.
- It's 9:00.

16:16.936 --> 16:18.229
- Why'd you bring him, Benny?
- 'Cause there's eight of us,
and he makes nine.

16:18.229 --> 16:20.231
- Why'd you bring him, Benny?
- 'Cause there's eight of us,
and he makes nine.

16:20.357 --> 16:22.901
Yeah, yeah, so would my sister,
but I didn't bring her.

16:23.026 --> 16:25.654
With nine guys we've got
a whole team, Yeah-Yeah.

16:26.780 --> 16:30.575
No. With Elswenger
we had a whole team.

16:30.659 --> 16:34.120
- Elswenger could catch.
- And throw.

16:34.245 --> 16:36.873
Come on, Benny, man.
He ain't game.

16:36.998 --> 16:40.043
- You saw the way he threw.
- Yeah.

16:40.126 --> 16:44.339
You already fill up all
the empty positions since
Elswenger moved to Arizona.

16:44.422 --> 16:47.425
Right. And now I get to rotate
eight positions instead of seven.

16:47.509 --> 16:51.638
- I need the practice, guys.
- You're the best on the team.
You don't need any practice.

16:51.763 --> 16:54.140
- No, you don't.
- You're the best, man.

16:54.265 --> 16:56.643
Come on, Benny, man.
The kid is...

16:56.768 --> 17:00.438
a L-7 weenie.

17:00.563 --> 17:04.108
Yeah, yeah.
Oscar Mayer even. Foot-long!

17:04.233 --> 17:07.904
Dodger dog! A weenie!

17:09.823 --> 17:12.409
What are you laughing at, Yeah-Yeah?
You run like a duck.

17:13.617 --> 17:15.829
Okay, okay, but I'm-- I'm--

17:15.954 --> 17:19.290
- Part of the game, right?
- Mmm, yeah.

17:19.415 --> 17:21.710
Now, how come
he don't get to be?

17:21.792 --> 17:23.877
- 'Cause he's a geek, man.
- He can't catch.

17:23.962 --> 17:27.007
Man, base up,
you blockheads.

17:32.512 --> 17:35.682
Smalls, you take
left center, okay?

17:35.807 --> 17:38.768
Okay. Um, where
exactly is that?

17:40.854 --> 17:42.772
It's over there, man.

17:49.279 --> 17:51.156
Here?

17:53.366 --> 17:55.285
That's left.
I said left center.

17:56.494 --> 17:58.788
Okay. Right.

17:58.872 --> 18:00.790
Here?

18:03.668 --> 18:06.171
Come on, Benny, man.

18:06.296 --> 18:09.883
He's never gonna catch the ball anyway.
Let's just play.

18:11.801 --> 18:15.597
- What a jerk.
- Yeah-Yeah, get two.

18:18.850 --> 18:20.894
Come on!
Throw it in here, Bertram!

18:23.355 --> 18:25.899
- Nice.
- Wow!

18:26.024 --> 18:27.901
Good job!

18:30.362 --> 18:33.156
- Hey, Smalls, throw it to second.
- Okay.

18:36.826 --> 18:40.914
- Come on, Benny.
He's never gonna catch it.
- He's not gonna catch it.

18:43.375 --> 18:46.294
Oh! I told you, Benny.
We told you.

18:50.590 --> 18:52.676
Come on, Benny.
Why'd you do that?

18:56.388 --> 19:00.016
A square, Benny.
The kid's a square.

19:06.272 --> 19:09.025
Come on. Throw it in.

19:09.109 --> 19:11.945
What the hell's he doing?

19:15.740 --> 19:17.701
I don't believe this.

19:21.121 --> 19:24.040
Here. Sorry. Sorry.

19:50.734 --> 19:52.610
You can throw it, you know.

19:55.113 --> 19:57.032
No.

19:57.115 --> 19:59.159
I can't.

19:59.284 --> 20:01.161
I don't know how.

20:03.121 --> 20:07.250
Thanks for taking me here,
but I think I'd better go.

20:07.375 --> 20:10.378
Hey, hey.
You think too much.

20:10.462 --> 20:12.380
I bet you get straight A's
and shit, huh?

20:12.464 --> 20:14.799
No, I got a "B" once.

20:14.924 --> 20:18.261
Actually an A-minus.
But it should've been a "B."

20:18.345 --> 20:21.014
Man, this is baseball.
You gotta stop thinking.

20:21.139 --> 20:23.016
You just have fun.

20:23.141 --> 20:26.019
I mean, if you were having fun,
you would've caught that ball.

20:29.272 --> 20:31.149
You ever have
a paper route?

20:31.274 --> 20:33.360
I helped a guy once.

20:34.986 --> 20:37.822
Okay. Well, chuck it like
you would throw a paper.

20:37.947 --> 20:41.242
When your arm gets here,
just let go.

20:41.326 --> 20:43.244
Just let go.
It's that easy.

20:44.496 --> 20:47.165
How do I catch it?

20:49.125 --> 20:52.796
Just stand there and stick your glove
out in the air.

20:52.879 --> 20:54.798
I'll take care of it.

20:54.881 --> 20:58.051
About time, Benny.
My clothes are going out of style.

20:58.176 --> 21:00.845
- They already are, Squints.
- Shut up!

21:01.888 --> 21:03.807
I told you, Benny.

21:06.476 --> 21:08.395
Smalls, throw it to second.

21:08.520 --> 21:10.897
Okay.

21:12.983 --> 21:15.318
Not again.

21:15.402 --> 21:17.529
We're wasting time, Benny.

21:19.197 --> 21:21.116
Please catch it.

21:29.499 --> 21:31.543
Please catch it.

21:31.668 --> 21:34.296
Please catch it.
Please catch it.

21:41.386 --> 21:43.305
Yeah!

21:45.265 --> 21:49.352
- All right!
- He's all right.

21:49.436 --> 21:52.063
I told you so, man.

21:56.401 --> 21:58.320
Okay.

21:58.403 --> 22:01.448
- Let's play some ball.
- Yeah, let's play some ball.

22:01.573 --> 22:05.035
All right.
I knew it... all the time.

22:08.747 --> 22:10.498
Yeah!

22:25.972 --> 22:28.058
I'll show you some more
tomorrow, okay?

22:28.141 --> 22:30.060
- Okay. Bye.
- You did good.

22:30.143 --> 22:32.062
See you later, Ham.
8:00 tomorrow.

22:32.145 --> 22:34.064
- 8:00, Benny?
- Yeah. See you later, Smalls.

22:34.147 --> 22:36.524
Bye. See you tomorrow.

22:36.608 --> 22:38.526
Benny, wait!

22:38.610 --> 22:42.322
- Your glove.
- Keep it, man.

22:42.447 --> 22:44.324
Thanks!

22:45.950 --> 22:48.244
Oh, yeah.
Hey, Smalls.

22:52.957 --> 22:57.253
Um, bring a T-shirt
and jeans tomorrow, okay?

22:57.337 --> 23:01.132
- Oh, um, you got a fireplace?
- Oh, yeah.

23:01.257 --> 23:03.176
Yeah, why?

23:03.301 --> 23:05.178
Throw that hat
in there, man.

23:05.303 --> 23:08.139
Oh, yeah. You know,
it was the only one I had.

23:08.223 --> 23:10.725
Not anymore.
Wear my old hat.

23:10.809 --> 23:12.727
8:00 tomorrow morning.

23:12.811 --> 23:16.189
Thanks, Benny.
Great. 8:00.

23:18.274 --> 23:20.151
Mom, guess what?

23:36.001 --> 23:39.546
Hamilton "The Babe" Porter.

23:39.671 --> 23:42.007
"Long-ball" Porter.

23:42.132 --> 23:44.009
Come on, DeNunez.

23:49.681 --> 23:53.143
Yeah, okay.
Yes, I see it. Yes.

23:58.523 --> 24:00.442
Whoa!

24:00.525 --> 24:03.570
You call that pitching?

24:03.695 --> 24:06.448
This is baseball,
not tennis.

24:06.531 --> 24:08.950
