- Make me one of those.

28:28.209 --> 28:30.128
Yeah, me too.

28:30.211 --> 28:33.840
- Then you stuff.
- I don't like that chocolate stuff.

28:33.965 --> 28:36.009
Kind of messy, but good.
Try some.

28:36.134 --> 28:38.720
Okay. Quiet, you guys.

28:38.803 --> 28:42.057
Shh! Shh!

28:42.140 --> 28:45.101
Quiet! Are you trying
to wake it up?

28:45.185 --> 28:47.771
It just went to bed.

28:47.896 --> 28:50.690
- What just went to bed?
- Shh!

28:50.815 --> 28:53.151
The Beast.

28:53.234 --> 28:55.820
- Oh, yeah!
- Shh!

28:55.945 --> 28:57.822
- Jeez.
- Dang.

28:57.947 --> 29:00.033
Shh.

29:01.159 --> 29:03.161
Now quiet.

29:05.121 --> 29:10.377
The legend of The Beast
goes back a long time...

29:11.670 --> 29:15.340
before any of us
could even pick up a baseball.

29:17.008 --> 29:21.846
Back to a place
called Mertle's Acres.

29:21.972 --> 29:26.851
It all started about, mmm,
20 years ago,

29:26.977 --> 29:30.814
when thieves kept stealing junk
from Mertle's Acres junkyard.

29:30.897 --> 29:34.275
So Mr. Mertle, the guy
that used to own the place,

29:34.359 --> 29:38.238
got him this new pup
from the dog pound.

29:38.363 --> 29:40.490
He fed him whole sides of beef...

29:40.615 --> 29:43.201
and turned the pup loose
in the junkyard.

29:43.326 --> 29:45.578
And the pup was grateful.

29:57.173 --> 30:00.552
And so, in a few weeks,
the pup grew into The Beast.

30:00.677 --> 30:04.180
And he grew big,
and he grew mean...

30:04.306 --> 30:08.476
so that he could protect the junkyard
with only one thing on his mind:

30:08.560 --> 30:11.229
to kill everyone
that broke in.

30:11.354 --> 30:15.775
And he did, and he liked it a lot!

30:15.900 --> 30:19.654
The Beast was the most perfect
junkyard dog that ever lived.

30:19.738 --> 30:22.866
A true killing machine.

30:22.991 --> 30:25.827
But after a while, the cops started
getting phone calls from people...

30:25.910 --> 30:28.705
reporting all the missing thieves,

30:28.788 --> 30:31.041
the ones The Beast had killed.

30:31.124 --> 30:33.918
It added up to about 120--

30:34.044 --> 30:36.296
173 guys.

30:36.421 --> 30:38.465
It's true.

30:38.590 --> 30:40.925
They never found a single body.

30:41.051 --> 30:44.137
Not one. Some people say
they all got away.

30:44.262 --> 30:47.015
But we all know
what really happened.

30:47.098 --> 30:49.059
The Beast ate them.

30:49.142 --> 30:52.979
He ate them bone and all.

30:53.104 --> 30:55.398
The Beast was too good
at his guard dog job,

30:55.482 --> 30:58.193
so the police said
he had to be retired.

30:58.276 --> 31:01.112
My grandpa, Squidman Palledorous,

31:01.196 --> 31:03.448
was police chiefback then.

31:03.573 --> 31:08.119
He ordered Mr. Mertle to turn
his backyard into a fortress...

31:08.244 --> 31:11.706
and chain up The Beast
and put him under the house...

31:11.790 --> 31:14.834
where he could never get out
to eat children and stuff.

31:14.959 --> 31:17.671
That's where he's been for 20 years.

31:17.796 --> 31:20.548
And that's where he'll be
for the rest of his life.

31:20.632 --> 31:23.677
Because Mr. Mertle
asked the cops how long...

31:23.802 --> 31:26.346
he had to keep The Beast
chained up like a slave,

31:26.471 --> 31:30.809
they said until forever.

31:30.934 --> 31:32.978
Forever. Forever.

31:32.978 --> 31:35.438
Forever. Forever.

31:35.522 --> 31:39.192
Forever.

31:39.317 --> 31:43.738
And so, The Beast sits there
under that lean-to,

31:43.822 --> 31:48.201
dreaming of the time when he can
break the chain and get out,

31:48.326 --> 31:51.913
dreaming of the time
he can chase and kill again.

31:53.164 --> 31:55.208
See, man? That's why
you can't go over there.

31:55.333 --> 31:58.003
Nobody ever has.
Nobody ever will.

31:58.128 --> 32:01.339
One kid did, but nobody
ever seen him again.

32:01.464 --> 32:04.676
- That ain't true.
- Yeah, it is.

32:08.388 --> 32:10.307
He got eaten.

32:10.390 --> 32:12.684
Nuh-uh.

32:12.767 --> 32:14.936
No. None of that's true.

32:15.020 --> 32:17.272
You guys are just making this up
to scare me.

32:17.355 --> 32:19.274
Oh, yeah?

32:21.359 --> 32:23.278
Stick your head
out that window...

32:23.361 --> 32:25.530
and look down.

32:28.658 --> 32:33.079
That night I
learned that more than 150 baseballs...

32:33.204 --> 32:36.291
had gone over that fence and not one
of them was ever seen again,

32:36.374 --> 32:38.293
even when some brave kid...

32:38.376 --> 32:40.670
worked up enough courage
to peek over.

32:40.754 --> 32:43.131
Because when they went over,
they vanished.

32:43.214 --> 32:45.133
I knew it was true.

32:45.216 --> 32:47.177
Because when I looked down in there,

32:47.260 --> 32:51.556
I didn't see a single solitary one.

32:54.225 --> 32:57.020
- He's down there.
- You bet he is.

32:57.103 --> 33:00.148
Whatever goes over that fence...

33:02.442 --> 33:04.361
stays there.

33:04.444 --> 33:07.989
It becomes the property
of The Beast...

33:08.073 --> 33:10.200
forever.

33:14.245 --> 33:16.915
- Come on, give it to me.
- No, I wanna carry it.

33:17.040 --> 33:19.417
- Come on. I paid for it.
- I wanna carry it.

33:19.501 --> 33:22.587
- Oh. Whoa!
- Give it to me.

33:22.712 --> 33:25.256
Jeez Louise.

33:25.382 --> 33:27.258
- What's the matter?
- Jeez.

33:37.894 --> 33:41.022
Wendy Peffercorn. Mmm.

33:42.357 --> 33:44.442
- Whoa!
- Wow!

34:04.296 --> 34:06.715
- Come on, let's go. We gotta get--
- No!

34:06.798 --> 34:09.384
We gotta get to the sandlot. Let's go.

34:12.304 --> 34:14.222
- Come on. Let's go.
- Okay.

34:16.181 --> 34:19.143
I'm sweating like a pig.

34:19.226 --> 34:21.146
Let's go! Come on!

34:24.858 --> 34:27.569
Where you guys been?
We've been waiting here forever already.

34:27.652 --> 34:29.612
Aw, Squints was pervin' a dish.

34:29.696 --> 34:32.991
- Shut up. I wasn't.
- Yeah, yeah, you were.

34:33.116 --> 34:37.203
Your tongue was hangin' out of
your head, and you was swoonin'.

34:37.329 --> 34:41.958
Oh, Wendy Peffercorn,
my darling lover girl.

34:42.042 --> 34:44.210
I said shut up!

34:44.335 --> 34:46.713
I've got a lot of things
on my mind.

34:49.882 --> 34:51.801
This pop isn't working, Benny.

34:51.885 --> 34:55.429
I'm baking like a toasted cheeser!
It's so hot here!

34:55.513 --> 34:59.351
It's 150 degrees out there.
You can't play baseball.

34:59.434 --> 35:02.479
- You have to call it for the day.
- You gotta listen to him, Benny.

35:02.562 --> 35:06.316
Vote then.
Anybody who wants to be...

35:06.399 --> 35:10.445
a "can't hack it" panty waist...

35:10.528 --> 35:13.948
who wears their mama's bra,
raise your hand.

35:14.032 --> 35:15.992
Yeah, I can handle that.

35:17.577 --> 35:19.788
Fine, fine, fine!

35:19.871 --> 35:21.790
Be like that.

35:21.873 --> 35:23.792
So what are we gonna do?

35:29.255 --> 35:32.550
Scam pool honeys!

35:32.717 --> 35:36.471
Benny would've
played ball all day, all night, rain,

35:36.554 --> 35:38.473
shine, tidal wave, whatever.

35:38.556 --> 35:41.059
Baseball was the only thing
he cared about.

35:41.142 --> 35:43.728
But of all the things
we ever did besides baseball,

35:43.853 --> 35:46.648
going to the pool
was what he tolerated best.

35:46.731 --> 35:49.275
Even though none of us had
ever seen a Playboy magazine,

35:49.401 --> 35:52.487
- which we constantly lied about,
- Hi.

35:52.570 --> 35:55.615
We figured going to the pool was
the next best thing to being there.

35:55.740 --> 35:58.952
I remember you.
Oh, sexy.

36:01.913 --> 36:04.040
Hey, girls.

36:09.546 --> 36:12.173
Cannonball!

36:19.306 --> 36:22.726
It wasn't really
the pool honeys like we said,

36:22.809 --> 36:27.230
because if any one of them
had come up to any one of us,
we'd have just peed our pants.

36:27.314 --> 36:29.607
We all went because--

36:29.733 --> 36:34.612
well, because Wendy Peffercorn
was the lifeguard.

36:50.920 --> 36:54.758
- Aw, man.
- Yeah, yeah. Too cool.

36:54.841 --> 36:56.801
She don't know what she's doing.

36:56.926 --> 36:58.803
She don't know what she's doing.

36:58.928 --> 37:01.139
Yeah, she does.

37:01.264 --> 37:03.933
She knows exactly
what she's doing.

37:04.017 --> 37:07.771
I've swum here every summer
of my adult life.

37:10.523 --> 37:13.234
And every summer,
there she is,

37:13.318 --> 37:18.782
lotioning, oiling,
oiling, lotioning.

37:18.865 --> 37:22.744
- One day it became too much...
- Smiling.

37:22.827 --> 37:25.747
- For Michael "Squints" Palledorous.
- Smiling!

37:25.830 --> 37:28.249
I can't take this no more!

37:28.333 --> 37:30.919
- Move!
- And he did the most desperate thing...

37:31.002 --> 37:33.254
- Lotioning, oiling.
- Any of us...

37:33.338 --> 37:35.298
