46:19.239 --> 46:21.157
Tomorrow.

46:21.241 --> 46:24.160
Noon. At our field.

46:24.244 --> 46:26.162
Be there, buffalo-butt breath.

46:26.246 --> 46:28.540
Count on it,
pee-drinking crap face!

46:28.665 --> 46:30.000
Yeah!

46:30.083 --> 46:32.335
Let's go!

46:41.219 --> 46:43.138
We're gonna kick
their butts tomorrow.

46:43.221 --> 46:45.140
Yeah!

46:46.683 --> 46:48.560
- Good job.
- Jerks.

46:50.854 --> 46:53.690
Play ball!

46:55.942 --> 46:57.861
Hurry up, batter.

46:57.944 --> 47:00.947
It's gonna be a short game,
and I gotta get home for lunch.

47:02.574 --> 47:04.617
That's one.

47:04.743 --> 47:09.247
You know, if I had a dog
as ugly as you,

47:09.372 --> 47:13.460
I'd shave his butt
and tell him to walk backwards.

47:13.585 --> 47:15.712
The heater.

47:15.795 --> 47:18.757
Here it comes.
I dare you.

47:18.840 --> 47:20.884
Strike three.
You're out.

47:20.967 --> 47:25.555
Hey, is that your sister
out there in left field, naked?

47:25.639 --> 47:27.974
- She's naked.
- Shut up, Porter!

47:28.099 --> 47:29.976
Hey, hey, hey.

47:30.101 --> 47:33.021
I'm just trying to have
a little friendly conversation.

47:33.104 --> 47:36.524
Come on. You think
she'd go out with me?

47:39.152 --> 47:40.904
Come on.
Show me your stuff.

47:41.029 --> 47:43.490
- Let's see what you got.
- Hey, batter, batter, batter!

47:43.615 --> 47:46.284
Take him out!

48:02.425 --> 48:05.679
- Come on!
- Bring it in!

48:16.314 --> 48:19.484
Oh! Beat ya.

48:22.028 --> 48:24.864
Throw it to third!

48:55.353 --> 48:58.523
We were all walking on air that night.

48:58.648 --> 49:00.525
It had been a solid victory.

49:00.650 --> 49:02.944
In fact, we beat the crap
out of those guys.

49:03.028 --> 49:05.363
So we all went to celebrate.

49:05.488 --> 49:08.199
And we did
the stupidest thing...

49:08.325 --> 49:10.243
any of us had ever done.

49:10.368 --> 49:13.330
Hey, guys, it's all on me tonight.

49:13.413 --> 49:15.332
Thanks, Benny!

49:15.415 --> 49:17.334
Nine tickets, please.

49:17.417 --> 49:19.336
- Hey, Benny.
- Thanks.

49:19.419 --> 49:22.339
- Hey, Benny.
- Benny.

49:22.422 --> 49:24.716
- Come on, you guys!
- What about me? Thanks.

49:24.841 --> 49:28.011
Aw, crap!
I almost forgot!

49:28.094 --> 49:30.221
- What?
- What?

49:33.350 --> 49:36.519
Chaw! I was saving it
for a good time.

49:36.603 --> 49:38.647
- What is it?
- Big Chief.

49:38.730 --> 49:40.649
The best!

49:40.732 --> 49:45.737
Jeez, Smalls. I suppose you don't
even know who The Babe is either.

49:47.697 --> 49:49.991
It's plug. Wad.
Chewing tobacco.

49:50.075 --> 49:52.661
- 'Baccy, man.
- What do you do with it?

49:54.913 --> 49:57.791
You're killing me, Smalls.

49:59.417 --> 50:01.836
- Chew it, of course. Yes.
- You do?

50:01.920 --> 50:04.631
Yeah, sure, man.
All the pros do it.

50:04.756 --> 50:07.217
Yeah, yeah.
Gives you tons of energy.

50:07.300 --> 50:10.720
- Let's dip. Let's dip.
- You got it, guys.

50:11.930 --> 50:14.641
Come on. I want some.

50:14.766 --> 50:17.102
- Mm. Mm.
- Mm.

50:17.227 --> 50:21.064
- The best.
- Let's ride!

50:21.147 --> 50:23.066
- Yeah!
- Yeah!

50:38.790 --> 50:40.709
Mm!

50:56.599 --> 50:59.769
- Yeah-hah!
- Yeah!

50:59.853 --> 51:03.231
- Whoo-hoo!
- Squints, this is the best!

51:03.315 --> 51:06.192
Wow! Yeah! Whoo!

51:06.318 --> 51:07.777
All right!

51:14.993 --> 51:16.911
Yeah!

51:43.396 --> 51:45.065
Blech!

52:29.401 --> 52:32.779
Oh, that feels better.

52:37.867 --> 52:40.912
I'll be back in an hour.
I'm gonna take your dad to the airport.

52:41.037 --> 52:42.956
Oh, okay.

52:43.039 --> 52:45.375
Honey, are you feeling all right?
You look kind of pale.

52:45.458 --> 52:47.377
- I'm fine, Mom.
- You sure?

52:47.460 --> 52:50.505
- I'm fine, really.
- All right.

52:50.630 --> 52:52.549
Listen, Scott.

52:54.968 --> 52:58.430
While I'm gone, you're the man
of the house. Understand?

52:58.555 --> 53:00.432
- Okay.
- Okay.

53:00.557 --> 53:03.351
- Where are you going?
- Chicago.

53:03.435 --> 53:05.437
On business for a week.

53:05.562 --> 53:09.024
- We'll take another stab at catch
when I get back, all right?
- Yeah, I guess so.

53:09.149 --> 53:11.568
- Take care of things for me.
- Okay.

53:11.651 --> 53:13.570
- All right?
- I will.

53:13.653 --> 53:16.489
Okay. Be a good boy.

53:16.573 --> 53:18.575
- I will.
- Okay.

53:25.832 --> 53:29.336
A couple days after
we all got over acting like big shots,

53:29.419 --> 53:33.840
we swore off the hard stuff forever
and just stuck to Bazooka.

53:33.923 --> 53:36.676
But the day we all got back
together for some baseball...

53:36.801 --> 53:40.889
was the day I got us into
the biggest pickle of all time,

53:40.972 --> 53:43.767
and it all started with an omen.

54:54.838 --> 54:56.756
Oh, man.

54:59.217 --> 55:02.178
I don't believe it.

55:02.262 --> 55:04.180
- Bitchin'.
- Nah, it ain't.

55:04.264 --> 55:06.182
Come on. Maybe two or three
guys in history...

55:06.308 --> 55:08.184
ever busted the guts out of a ball.

55:08.310 --> 55:12.105
- Must be an omen.
- All's it means is that
we can't play no more.

55:12.188 --> 55:15.358
It's only 12:00, and I just ruined
the whole day for us.

55:15.483 --> 55:18.445
No, you didn't. That's the most
amazing thing I ever saw.

55:18.528 --> 55:20.780
- Yeah.
- Anybody got any money?

55:20.864 --> 55:24.117
No.
- Then it ain't okay, 'cause
now we can't play no more.

55:24.200 --> 55:26.119
Yeah, we can.

55:26.202 --> 55:29.205
What, you got 98 extra cents
lying around, Smalls?

55:29.289 --> 55:33.293
- No, but I got a ball.
- Go get it!

55:49.517 --> 55:52.729
I got it, guys! I got it!
I got the ball, guys!

55:52.812 --> 55:54.731
I got it. Right here, guys.

55:54.814 --> 55:57.359
I got the ball. I got it.

55:57.484 --> 56:00.028
- Here, Benny. I got it.
- Bitchin'. Your ball, your ups.

56:00.153 --> 56:02.072
- Here you go.
- Okay.

56:02.155 --> 56:05.367
All right. Come on.
Kenny, here.

56:05.450 --> 56:07.369
Come on. Yeah, come on!

56:07.452 --> 56:09.996
Batter up!

56:10.080 --> 56:12.207
Your fly's open.

56:14.167 --> 56:16.336
There's one.

56:19.047 --> 56:21.049
One, two, three.

56:21.132 --> 56:23.385
Three strikes, three pitches.

56:23.468 --> 56:25.387
Hey, batter, batter, batter!

56:25.470 --> 56:29.057
- Come on, Smalls!
- Hey, batter, batter, batter!

56:31.685 --> 56:33.687
Oh, my. Oh, man.

56:35.105 --> 56:37.023
- Run!
- Yes!

56:37.107 --> 56:40.402
Way to go, school meat!
I taught him everything.

56:43.989 --> 56:47.075
Oh, man, that was great.
That went clear over.

56:49.411 --> 56:52.622
Hey, uh, Smalls,
third base is that way.

56:52.706 --> 56:54.624
Hey, Smalls. Smalls.

56:55.875 --> 56:59.212
- Go to third.
- Oh, no. Oh, no.

56:59.296 --> 57:02.465
Yeah! Nice hit, Smalls.
Nice hit. Yeah!

57:02.590 --> 57:06.011
- Oh, no.
- It's outta here!
Who's got the big bat now?

57:06.136 --> 57:09.097
- Smalls! Smalls! Smalls!
- Smalls?

57:09.180 --> 57:11.266
You forgot to turn.

57:11.349 --> 57:13.601
You go to third base!

57:15.812 --> 57:17.772
Smalls--

57:19.024 --> 57:20.942
What the hell's he doing?

57:21.026 --> 57:23.987
Maybe the shock of his first homer
was just too much for him.

57:24.112 --> 57:26.906
Yeah.

57:28.325 --> 57:32.162
Smalls.

57:33.747 --> 57:35.999
Smalls? Smalls.

57:51.181 --> 57:55.018
- We got to get that ball back.
- Oh, yeah, right.

57:55.101 --> 57:57.937
- Good one, Smalls.
- Yeah, good one, Smalls.

57:58.021 --> 58:01.107
Hey, forget about it, man.
Let's get another ball.

58:01.191 --> 58:03.026
No, you don't understand!

58:03.109 --> 58:07.155
Sure, we do. You feel bad
'cause you belted a homer.
Now we can't play no more.

58:07.280 --> 58:09.949
No, you don't understand!
That wasn't my ball!

58:14.120 --> 58:16.998
What do you mean,
that wasn't your ball?

58:17.082 --> 58:19.292
It was my stepdad's.

58:19.376 --> 58:21.503
I stole it from his trophy room.

58:21.628 --> 58:24.089
It was a present or something.
Somebody gave it to him.

58:24.214 --> 58:26.383
We gotta get it back.
He's gonna kill me!

58:26.508 --> 58:29.427
Ohh.

58:29.552 --> 58:32.180
Listen to me, Smalls.

58:32.263 --> 58:34.724
It's a matter of life and death.

58:34.849 --> 58:38.061
Where did your old man
get that ball?

58:38.144 --> 58:41.398
What? I don't know.
Some lady gave it to him.

58:41.481 --> 58:44.025
- Why?
- What? Some lady?

58:44.150 --> 58:47.612
Yeah. She even signed her name on it.
Some lady named...

58:47.737 --> 58:49.864
Ruth, Baby Ruth.

58:49.948 --> 58:52.158
Babe Ruth?

59:14.639 --> 59:16.850
No!

59:22.314 --> 59:24.107
The Beast got it.

59:24.190 --> 59:27.736
- You're dead as a doornail, Smalls.
- You're dead as a doornail.

59:27.819 --> 59:31.281
Smalls, you mean to tell me that you
went home and swiped a ball...

59:31.406 --> 59:33.867
that was signed by Babe Ruth,

59:33.950 --> 59:37.454
- and you brought it here
and actually played with it?
- Actually played with it?

59:37.579 --> 59:42.125
- Yeah, but I was gonna bring it back.
- But it was signed by Babe Ruth.

59:42.250 --> 59:46.421
Yeah. Yeah. Yeah.
You keep telling me that. Who is she?

59:46.504 --> 59:48.298
What?

59:49.549 --> 59:51.593
What?

59:51.676 --> 59:55.263
- The Sultan of Swat.
- The King of Crash.

59:55.347 --> 59:57.932
- The Colossus of Clout.
- The Colossus of Clout.

59:58.016 --> 59:59.976
Babe Ruth!

01:00:00.101 --> 01:00:03.355
The Great Bambino!

01:00:04.564 --> 01:00:06.983
Oh, my God!
You mean that's the same guy?

01:00:07.108 --> 01:00:08.985
Yes!

01:00:09.110 --> 01:00:12.989
Smalls, Babe Ruth is the greatest
baseball player that ever lived.

01:00:13.114 --> 01:00:16.117
People say he was less than a god
but more than a man.

01:00:16.201 --> 01:00:18.703
You know, like Hercules
or something.

01:00:18.828 --> 01:00:22.499
That ball you just aced
to The Beast is worth,

01:00:22.624 --> 01:00:24.918
well, more than your whole life.

01:00:26.670 --> 01:00:30.131
I don't feel so good.

01:00:30.256 --> 01:00:34.010
- Uh-oh, fan him.
- Give him air, give him air.

01:00:34.094 --> 01:00:36.304
We have to get that ball back.

01:00:38.556 --> 01:00:41.810
- When does your old man
get home from work?
- He's gone on business.

01:00:41.893 --> 01:00:45.814
Out of town.
But he could be back anytime.

01:00:45.897 --> 01:00:47.816
All right.
Find out when.

01:00:47.899 --> 01:00:50.819
And, guys, spread out and look
for bottles and cash 'em in.

01:00:50.902 --> 01:00:53.738
We need 98 cents.
We gotta buy us a ball.

01:00:53.863 --> 01:00:55.907
Yeah!

01:01:01.705 --> 01:01:04.916
- Come on. Let's go!
- Go, go, go, go! Move, move!

01:01:05.041 --> 01:01:08.503
Come on. Open it up!
Hurry up, hurry up!

01:01:08.586 --> 01:01:11.298
- Give me the ball.
- Give me something to write with.

01:01:11.381 --> 01:01:14.384
- I got a pencil.
- Give me a pen, not a pencil!

01:01:14.509 --> 01:01:16.511
- Sorry.
- I got a pen.

01:01:18.263 --> 01:01:20.181
Babe--

01:01:20.265 --> 01:01:22.934
- Baby Ruthie?
- It says, "Babe Ruth."

01:01:23.059 --> 01:01:26.187
- I don't know, Benny, man.
- Yeah, boy, that looks pretty crappy.

01:01:26.271 --> 01:01:28.356
It doesn't matter
what it looks like.

01:01:28.440 --> 01:01:30.358
His mom's never gonna know
the difference.

01:01:30.442 --> 01:01:33.695
- This'll just buy us
some time, you dorks.
- Okay, come on.

01:01:50.795 --> 01:01:53.381
- Scotty?
- Uh, in here, Mom.

01:01:55.091 --> 01:01:57.844
Oh, hi, honey.
What are you doing in here?

01:01:57.927 --> 01:02:00.347
Uh, just looking at Bill's--

01:02:00.430 --> 01:02:02.432
I mean, uh, Dad's baseball.

01:02:02.557 --> 01:02:05.852
You know he doesn't like
you to touch his things.

01:02:07.312 --> 01:02:09.439
Yeah. I-- I know. Sorry, Mom.

01:02:09.564 --> 01:02:13.443
Has he ever told you about that ball?

01:02:13.568 --> 01:02:16.696
Uh, no. Uh, not really.

01:02:16.780 --> 01:02:20.950
I-- I don't think so.
No, no, no, he hasn't at all.

01:02:21.076 --> 01:02:23.745
I don't-- I don't know
anything about it.

01:02:23.828 --> 01:02:26.623
Babe Ruth signed that ball.
He was...

01:02:26.706 --> 01:02:28.958
the greatest baseball player
who ever lived.

01:02:29.042 --> 01:02:32.671
- Oh. Really?
- He sure is.

01:02:33.880 --> 01:02:36.800
Your dad's father gave it to him.

01:02:36.925 --> 01:02:39.302
Maybe someday he'll give it to you.

01:02:40.512 --> 01:02:42.847
Oh.

01:02:42.973 --> 01:02:44.849
Neat.

01:02:44.975 --> 01:02:47.519
It was salt in an open wound.

01:02:47.644 --> 01:02:49.896
Even my own mom, a grown-up girl,

01:02:49.980 --> 01:02:52.565
knew who Babe Ruth was.

01:02:52.732 --> 01:02:55.276
I was dead meat.

01:02:55.360 --> 01:02:58.822
We had thought that that ball Benny
had busted the guts out of...

01:02:58.947 --> 01:03:01.324
meant something amazing
was gonna happen.

01:03:01.449 --> 01:03:03.785
Now I just figured
it meant my life was over.

01:03:03.868 --> 01:03:05.954
Hey, I got it!

01:03:06.037 --> 01:03:08.164
Why don't we just go over...

01:03:08.289 --> 01:03:11.418
and knock on the door and ask
Mr. Mertle if he can get it for us?

01:03:11.501 --> 01:03:15.672
Are you out of your mind? Mr. Mertle's
the meanest old man that ever lived.

01:03:15.797 --> 01:03:19.467
He's the one who made
The Beast eat that kid.

01:03:20.719 --> 01:03:24.347
It's not an option, Smalls.
Forget about it!

01:03:24.472 --> 01:03:27.934
Oh, okay. Sorry.
I -- I will.

01:03:28.018 --> 01:03:30.270
Let's just look out the window.

01:03:30.353 --> 01:03:32.480
Good idea.

01:04:00.050 --> 01:04:03.678
- He's daring us.
- We're on his territory now.

01:04:03.803 --> 01:04:05.722
Anybody got any bright ideas?

01:04:05.847 --> 01:04:09.434
After we'd
all thought about it real hard,

01:04:09.559 --> 01:04:12.729
we had absolutely no idea
what the hell we were gonna do.

01:04:12.812 --> 01:04:14.856
So things started primitively.

01:04:18.151 --> 01:04:21.237
Go.

01:04:25.700 --> 01:04:28.703
- Farther.
- Farther, okay.

01:04:35.502 --> 01:04:39.255
- Just a little bit farther.
- Farther. Farther.

01:04:40.548 --> 01:04:43.843
Aah!

01:04:43.927 --> 01:04:47.013
Oh, no! Aah!

01:04:58.400 --> 01:05:01.027
Farther.

01:05:04.114 --> 01:05:08.284
Go to the right a little bit.
Put the back to the right.

01:05:12.163 --> 01:05:14.374
A little bit farther.

01:05:14.457 --> 01:05:17.085
- Farther?
- Guys, I see it. Turn, turn.

01:05:20.964 --> 01:05:23.383
Almost.

01:05:25.218 --> 01:05:28.054
You got it. Pull it back.

01:05:28.138 --> 01:05:30.765
- I got it!
- Got it, guys.

01:05:30.890 --> 01:05:33.935
Oh, my God!

01:05:34.060 --> 01:05:36.604
Pull it back! Aah!

01:05:58.043 --> 01:06:02.505
I think we've seriously
underestimated The Beast.

01:06:02.631 --> 01:06:06.176
Obviously, we're dealing
with a superior intelligence.

01:06:09.346 --> 01:06:12.515
- Power.
- Okay, guys, almost ready.

01:06:12.599 --> 01:06:14.517
We're connecting power now.

01:06:14.601 --> 01:06:17.145
Power connected.

01:06:33.286 --> 01:06:35.205
Okay, we're ready.

01:06:35.330 --> 01:06:37.832
Initiate retrieval suction.

01:06:37.916 --> 01:06:38.958
Initiate retrieval suction.

01:06:38.958 --> 01:06:40.627
Initiate retrieval suction.

01:06:40.710 --> 01:06:44.673
- Prepare to initiate
retrieval suction number one.
- Okay. Get ready, guys.

01:06:44.756 --> 01:06:46.967
Initiate retrieval suction
number one.

01:06:47.050 --> 01:06:49.552
Initiating retrieval suction
number one now!

01:06:53.723 --> 01:06:56.184
- Fire number two.
- Initiate number two.

01:06:56.267 --> 01:06:58.186
Firing two now!

01:07:01.606 --> 01:07:05.193
- Fire number three.
- Number three now!

01:07:05.276 --> 01:07:07.696
Whoa!

01:07:10.198 --> 01:07:13.201
Ha! You got it.
Haul it up.

01:07:13.284 --> 01:07:15.245
All right!

01:07:20.208 --> 01:07:23.044
Pull it up.

01:07:33.596 --> 01:07:38.727
- What's going on, Squints?
- The pipe-- it's pinched shut.

01:07:40.729 --> 01:07:44.524
- Turn it off, man!
- I can't! They're shorting out!

01:07:44.607 --> 01:07:47.235
What the hell is that noise?

01:07:47.319 --> 01:07:50.572
The vacs are clogged. I don't know
about you, but I'm getting outta here.

01:07:50.655 --> 01:07:52.615
Let's go!

01:07:52.699 --> 01:07:55.952
Oh, no! Aah!

01:07:57.078 --> 01:07:58.955
Aah!

01:08:04.294 --> 01:08:06.630
Aah!

01:08:06.713 --> 01:08:10.634
Aah! Aah!

01:08:10.717 --> 01:08:13.136
They're gonna blow! Aah!

01:08:24.773 --> 01:08:26.649
Aah!

01:08:26.774 --> 01:08:29.319
Incoming!

01:08:58.014 --> 01:09:03.185
We've been going about this all wrong.

01:09:03.269 --> 01:09:06.439
I blame myself.

01:09:06.523 --> 01:09:08.441
We need total surprise.

01:09:08.524 --> 01:09:13.279
An airborne attack.
The Beast will never expect it.

01:09:13.363 --> 01:09:14.990
Yeah.

01:09:25.207 --> 01:09:29.004
- It's clear.
- Take me up.

01:09:53.903 --> 01:09:55.822
Let me down slow.

01:10:02.871 --> 01:10:05.373
- A little slower.
- Go slow.

01:10:05.457 --> 01:10:07.459
Go.

01:10:07.584 --> 01:10:09.544
Yeah, let me down.
Almost there.

01:10:09.669 --> 01:10:13.214
He's almost there.

01:10:18.011 --> 01:10:20.138
Let me down right over it.

01:10:20.263 --> 01:10:22.724
Let him down right overit.

01:10:38.782 --> 01:10:40.700
Ewww.

01:10:42.452 --> 01:10:45.080
Okay, I got it.
Get me outta here.

01:10:45.163 --> 01:10:47.415
Pull him up.

01:10:53.630 --> 01:10:55.924
I-- I-- I--

01:10:56.007 --> 01:10:59.511
- Hey, pull him up!
- Aah! Aah!

01:10:59.636 --> 01:11:02.222
Aah!

01:11:04.766 --> 01:11:07.227
Aah!

01:11:07.310 --> 01:11:10.647
Aah!

01:11:17.112 --> 01:11:19.072
It was my last chance.

01:11:19.155 --> 01:11:22.492
So we quit messing around
and pulled out all the stops.

01:11:22.617 --> 01:11:25.161
I collected every piece
of erector set I had,

01:11:25.286 --> 01:11:27.998
and it finally became...

01:11:28.123 --> 01:11:31.167
science against nature.

01:11:43.513 --> 01:11:47.684
Okay, go with me on the launch.
Come on, Squints.

01:11:51.396 --> 01:11:53.815
- Prepare to launch.
- Prepare to launch.

01:11:53.898 --> 01:11:56.192
Prepare to launch. Launching.

01:11:56.276 --> 01:11:58.028
Launch.

01:12:23.053 --> 01:12:25.388
Okay, you're on the ground.

01:12:27.724 --> 01:12:29.851
Moving forward.

01:12:47.619 --> 01:12:50.163
- You went too far. Go back.
- Reverse. It's too far.

01:12:50.246 --> 01:12:51.831
Reverse.

01:12:53.667 --> 01:12:56.086
Stop.

01:12:56.211 --> 01:12:58.254
Drop catapult.

01:13:03.259 --> 01:13:06.262
- The catapult is dropped.
- Open catapult.

01:13:06.388 --> 01:13:09.015
We're gonna get it. I know it.

01:13:09.099 --> 01:13:10.892
Opening.

01:13:15.563 --> 01:13:17.941
Forward.

01:13:25.115 --> 01:13:27.534
Close catapult.

01:13:29.035 --> 01:13:32.539
- Catapult's closed.
- We're gonna get it. Come on.

01:13:33.915 --> 01:13:37.794
Aah! Fire, fire, fire!

01:13:44.467 --> 01:13:46.928
I got it! I got it! I got it!

01:13:51.057 --> 01:13:53.768
Aah!

01:14:23.006 --> 01:14:25.967
My life... was over.

01:14:26.092 --> 01:14:28.762
Just as Bill had finally
warmed up to me...

01:14:28.845 --> 01:14:30.972
and asked me to be
the man of the house,

01:14:31.097 --> 01:14:35.852
I had to knock a priceless chunk of
history into the clutches of a monster.

01:14:35.935 --> 01:14:38.563
Great.

01:14:38.688 --> 01:14:42.067
I had a dream that night
about a giant baseball...

01:14:42.192 --> 01:14:44.235
that was signed by Babe Ruth...

01:14:44.361 --> 01:14:46.821
falling out of the sky
and hammering me into the ground...

01:14:46.946 --> 01:14:49.449
like a railroad spike.

01:14:49.532 --> 01:14:51.534
I didn't know what that meant,

01:14:51.618 --> 01:14:55.872
but Benny had a dream that night too,
and his was a lot more helpful.

01:15:02.170 --> 01:15:04.881
Who's there?

01:15:09.094 --> 01:15:12.889
Don't go pee in your pants.
I'm just here to give you a hand.

01:15:12.973 --> 01:15:16.184
- B-But you're--
- Dead?

01:15:16.267 --> 01:15:18.228
Legends never die, kid.

01:15:18.311 --> 01:15:20.230
But you're really him.

01:15:21.815 --> 01:15:23.733
You're The Babe.

01:15:25.068 --> 01:15:28.405
The Sultan of Swat.
The King of Crash.

01:15:28.488 --> 01:15:31.074
Of Crash, and a hundred
other dopey names.

01:15:31.199 --> 01:15:33.576
Forget about that stuff, kid.
We ain't got much time.

01:15:33.702 --> 01:15:36.705
- I'm here 'cause you're in
some kind of a pickle, right?
- Yeah.

01:15:36.788 --> 01:15:39.791
A baseball with
my John Hancock on it...

01:15:39.916 --> 01:15:41.876
went over a fence and you
can't get it back, right?

01:15:41.960 --> 01:15:44.921
Yeah, right.

01:15:45.046 --> 01:15:48.550
- Then just hop over there and get it.
- Wait, wait!

01:15:54.472 --> 01:15:56.599
- I can't.
- Can't what?

01:15:58.268 --> 01:16:01.229
- I can't go into that backyard.
- Why not?

01:16:02.480 --> 01:16:04.858
There's a beast back there.

01:16:06.192 --> 01:16:08.320
What kind?

01:16:08.445 --> 01:16:11.906
A giant gorilla-dog thing
that ate one kid already.

01:16:12.032 --> 01:16:15.118
Is that a fact?
Sit down, kid.

01:16:17.287 --> 01:16:19.372
Sit down.

01:16:25.587 --> 01:16:28.465
Let me tell you something, kid.

01:16:28.590 --> 01:16:32.052
Everybody gets one chance
to do something great.

01:16:32.135 --> 01:16:35.430
Most people never take the chance,
either 'cause they're too scared...

01:16:35.513 --> 01:16:38.099
or they don't recognize it
when it spits on their shoes.

01:16:38.224 --> 01:16:40.894
This is your big chance,

01:16:40.977 --> 01:16:43.229
and you shouldn't let it go by.

01:16:43.313 --> 01:16:47.150
Remember when you busted the guts
out of the ball the other day?

01:16:47.275 --> 01:16:51.154
Someone's telling you something, kid.
If I was you, I'd listen.

01:16:52.739 --> 01:16:55.158
Yeah. But what?

01:16:55.241 --> 01:16:58.078
You're the one with the rubber legs.

01:16:58.161 --> 01:17:00.163
Figure it out.

01:17:01.748 --> 01:17:04.125
"Henry Aaron."

01:17:04.209 --> 01:17:07.462
- I don't know why, but can I have this?
- Sure, yeah.

01:17:07.545 --> 01:17:09.464
Thanks.

01:17:11.549 --> 01:17:13.843
Wait.

01:17:15.845 --> 01:17:20.600
You're saying I should hop over
that fence and pickle The Beast?

01:17:22.185 --> 01:17:26.356
Think about that, kid.
I'll see you later.

01:17:30.652 --> 01:17:34.280
Remember, kid, there's heroes
and there's legends.

01:17:34.364 --> 01:17:36.992
Heroes get remembered,

01:17:37.117 --> 01:17:39.160
but legends never die.

01:17:39.244 --> 01:17:43.164
Follow your heart, kid,
and you'll never go wrong.

01:17:47.002 --> 01:17:49.254
I had a dream. Get dressed.
We're going to the sandlot.

01:17:49.379 --> 01:17:51.548
Okay. Wait.
I'll get my stuff.

01:18:00.390 --> 01:18:03.143
Only one kid
in history had ever attempted...

01:18:03.226 --> 01:18:05.854
what Benny was about to,

01:18:05.937 --> 01:18:07.897
and he got eaten.

01:18:07.981 --> 01:18:11.359
So we were worried--
real worried--

01:18:11.443 --> 01:18:14.279
even when Benny brought out
the secret weapon:

01:18:14.404 --> 01:18:18.575
shoes guaranteed to make a kid
run faster and jump higher,

01:18:18.700 --> 01:18:20.577
P.F. Flyers.

01:18:20.702 --> 01:18:23.872
We can't let him do this, man.

01:18:41.181 --> 01:18:42.891
Benny, wait.

01:18:44.100 --> 01:18:46.019
It's okay.

01:18:46.102 --> 01:18:48.063
It was my fault.

01:18:50.148 --> 01:18:52.317
You don't have to do this.

01:18:52.442 --> 01:18:56.071
Yeah. Come on, Benny, man. You don't
have to do it. Forget about it.

01:18:56.196 --> 01:18:59.032
It's like committing suicide,
Benny. Don't do it.

01:18:59.115 --> 01:19:01.451
- Yeah, don't do it, Benny.
- Yeah.

01:19:01.576 --> 01:19:03.286
Don't do it.
It's suicide.

01:19:03.411 --> 01:19:05.622
Yeah, I do, Smalls.

01:19:07.082 --> 01:19:09.542
I have to do this.

01:19:17.926 --> 01:19:19.803
Heroes get remembered,

01:19:19.928 --> 01:19:21.930
but legends never die.

01:19:22.013 --> 01:19:25.809
Follow your heart, kid,
and you'll never go wrong.

01:21:33.103 --> 01:21:35.730
Whoa!

01:21:38.525 --> 01:21:41.444
- Yeah! Yeah!
- Yeah!

01:21:41.569 --> 01:21:44.948
- Yeah! All right, Benny!
- Oh, shit!

01:21:58.086 --> 01:22:02.132
Come on! What are we waiting for?
Let's get him!

01:22:10.056 --> 01:22:13.601
A werewolf can be killed
only with a silver bullet...

01:22:13.727 --> 01:22:16.313
or a silver knife
or a stick...

01:22:16.438 --> 01:22:18.940
- with a silver handle.
- You're insane.

01:22:24.446 --> 01:22:26.406
Aah!

01:22:27.657 --> 01:22:29.117
Ohh!

01:22:29.200 --> 01:22:32.746
- The wolf bit you, didn't he?
- Yeah, he did.

01:22:37.334 --> 01:22:41.171
Go now.
And heaven help you.

01:23:51.616 --> 01:23:55.537
Look out! Aah!

01:23:58.456 --> 01:24:01.418
Hey! Hey!

01:24:07.132 --> 01:24:10.051
Hey, hey, hey! Kids!

01:24:12.762 --> 01:24:15.015
Put it down.
Careful, careful.

01:24:16.391 --> 01:24:18.935
Whoa, whoa, whoa!

01:24:19.060 --> 01:24:22.230
Whoa, whoa, whoa!

01:24:32.782 --> 01:24:34.743
Mommy, Mommy, look.
A doggy!

01:24:37.454 --> 01:24:41.291
Ooh, a big doggy.

01:24:45.754 --> 01:24:48.256
- Ohh!
- Look out! Look out!

01:24:48.381 --> 01:24:50.717
Look out!
Sandlot, sandlot, sandlot!

01:24:50.800 --> 01:24:53.053
Sandlot!
Let's go!

01:24:53.136 --> 01:24:56.431
This way! Sandlot!
Shortcut, you guys! Let's go!

01:25:10.695 --> 01:25:12.989
Where is he?

01:25:13.114 --> 01:25:14.991
Does anyone see him?

01:25:15.116 --> 01:25:17.285
I don't see him.

01:25:22.916 --> 01:25:25.210
There he is!

01:25:33.259 --> 01:25:35.178
Oh, no.

01:25:57.617 --> 01:26:01.538
Aah!

01:26:13.550 --> 01:26:15.635
Look out!

01:26:45.582 --> 01:26:48.251
Oh, man.

01:26:48.376 --> 01:26:50.420
Oh, man.

01:27:00.930 --> 01:27:02.849
Come on, guys.
Help me!

01:27:02.932 --> 01:27:04.851
Please!

01:27:07.562 --> 01:27:12.275
Benny! Benny,
help me, please! He's hurt!

01:27:15.070 --> 01:27:17.781
Come on.
I can't lift it.

01:28:14.754 --> 01:28:16.673
Let's go.

01:28:29.853 --> 01:28:32.022
Wow!

01:28:35.817 --> 01:28:37.736
Aw.

01:28:44.576 --> 01:28:47.996
- Wow!
- Now we can play forever.

01:29:10.393 --> 01:29:12.270
Hello?

01:29:12.395 --> 01:29:14.689
This is bad.

01:29:14.773 --> 01:29:16.691
This is very bad.

01:29:16.775 --> 01:29:19.861
Um, we-- we--
we brought your dog home.

01:29:19.986 --> 01:29:22.489
Hercules?

01:29:22.572 --> 01:29:24.491
How'd he get out?

01:29:24.574 --> 01:29:28.411
I'm telling you guys,
we should've just turned it loose.

01:29:29.704 --> 01:29:32.040
Um, uh, well, uh-- We, uh--

01:29:32.123 --> 01:29:36.419
What happened was, we hit a baseball
into your yard. We tried to get it back.

01:29:36.544 --> 01:29:40.423
- So you're the ones that've
been making all that racket.
- Yes, sir.

01:29:40.548 --> 01:29:42.634
You get it?

01:29:42.759 --> 01:29:45.971
Um, y-yeah.

01:29:48.640 --> 01:29:50.809
Well, first time...

01:29:50.934 --> 01:29:54.729
that anybody ever got
the best of old Hercules.

01:29:54.813 --> 01:29:58.233
Why didn't you just knock on the door?
I'd have gotten it for you.

01:29:58.316 --> 01:30:00.110
Oh, my God!

01:30:00.235 --> 01:30:02.278
I can't believe you!

01:30:02.404 --> 01:30:06.116
- We got the ball back, didn't we?
- We almost got killed!

01:30:06.241 --> 01:30:09.703
Didn't we get the ball back?
Just shut up!

01:30:11.788 --> 01:30:13.707
We got the ball back.

01:30:18.670 --> 01:30:21.423
Thanks for bringing him home.

01:30:21.506 --> 01:30:24.092
Come on in.

01:30:28.305 --> 01:30:30.849
We'll talk about this baseball.

01:30:30.974 --> 01:30:32.851
Come on.

01:30:42.485 --> 01:30:44.988
You in trouble,
aren't you, son?

01:30:47.490 --> 01:30:50.201
Yeah, well, uh,
that was my stepdad's ball.

01:30:50.327 --> 01:30:53.413
I took it without asking.

01:30:53.496 --> 01:30:57.000
- It was signed by Babe Ruth.
- George signed this?

01:30:57.125 --> 01:30:59.836
George Herman Ruth?
Yeah.

01:30:59.961 --> 01:31:03.965
I take it back. You're not in trouble.
You're dead where you stand.

01:31:06.593 --> 01:31:08.511
Hold on.

01:31:10.430 --> 01:31:12.474
Hold on.

01:31:28.198 --> 01:31:30.533
Here.

01:31:32.118 --> 01:31:35.121
I'll trade ya.

01:31:35.205 --> 01:31:38.625
That's nice of you, but that ball
really is signed by Babe Ruth.

01:31:38.708 --> 01:31:43.046
So's this one, with the rest
of the 1927 Yankees.

01:31:45.840 --> 01:31:49.302
Oh, man.
Murderer's Row!

01:31:49.386 --> 01:31:51.888
Lou Gehrig!

01:31:51.972 --> 01:31:55.350
Babe Ruth! But why would you trade?

01:31:55.433 --> 01:31:57.102
That one's all chewed up.

01:31:57.227 --> 01:32:00.021
I got a lot of good stuff.
Look at that stuff.

01:32:00.105 --> 01:32:03.358
Besides, you need it
more than I do.

01:32:17.455 --> 01:32:19.374
You knew Babe Ruth?

01:32:19.457 --> 01:32:23.420
George? I sure did.
And he knew me.

01:32:23.503 --> 01:32:27.215
He was almost as great
a hitter as I was.

01:32:27.340 --> 01:32:31.344
- I would've broken his record, but--
- You went blind.

01:32:31.428 --> 01:32:33.888
Yep. I used to crowd the plate...

01:32:33.972 --> 01:32:37.851
so the strike zone
almost disappeared.

01:32:37.934 --> 01:32:40.437
Pitchers hate that.

01:32:41.771 --> 01:32:44.899
That's the way I played--
100 % all the time.

01:32:44.983 --> 01:32:48.153
Baseball was life.

01:32:48.278 --> 01:32:51.239
And I was good at it, real good.

01:32:51.364 --> 01:32:53.783
And then... one day,

01:32:53.908 --> 01:32:55.952
a high fast one, and pow,

01:32:56.077 --> 01:32:58.204
lights went out.

01:33:01.207 --> 01:33:04.002
I don't think we
could take this ball.

01:33:04.127 --> 01:33:06.046
I'll tell you what.

01:33:06.129 --> 01:33:10.759
You guys come by once a week
and talk baseball with me,
we'll call it an even trade.

01:33:15.847 --> 01:33:17.766
Deal!

01:33:19.601 --> 01:33:22.646
Even though
Bill loved the Murderer's Row ball,

01:33:22.771 --> 01:33:25.398
he was still plenty mad
about me having swiped...

01:33:25.482 --> 01:33:29.235
his Babe Ruth autographed ball
and ruining it.

01:33:29.319 --> 01:33:33.281
So I didn't feel too bad when
he grounded me for a week...

01:33:33.365 --> 01:33:35.659
instead of the rest of my life.

01:33:35.742 --> 01:33:37.911
Wow!

01:33:37.994 --> 01:33:40.288
Things worked out
between me and him.

01:33:40.372 --> 01:33:42.791
And from then on,
I didn't have any trouble...

01:33:42.874 --> 01:33:46.628
just calling him Dad
all the time.

01:33:46.711 --> 01:33:50.590
We all lived together
in the neighborhood
for a couple of more years--

01:33:50.674 --> 01:33:53.802
mostly through junior high school--
and every summer was great.

01:33:53.927 --> 01:33:57.263
But none of them ever came
close to that first one.

01:33:57.347 --> 01:33:59.432
When one guy would move away,

01:33:59.516 --> 01:34:02.602
we never replaced him
on the team with anyone else.

01:34:02.686 --> 01:34:06.106
We just kept the game going
like he was still there.

01:34:06.189 --> 01:34:08.441
You're starting
to hurt my hand.

01:34:08.525 --> 01:34:10.610
Don't miss it!

01:34:10.777 --> 01:34:13.113
It was weird that Benny said...

01:34:13.196 --> 01:34:17.617
Babe Ruth was like the Hercules
of baseball, and The Beast's
name ended up being Hercules.

01:34:17.701 --> 01:34:20.203
None of us could figure out
what that meant,

01:34:20.286 --> 01:34:22.539
but we were all amazed by it.

01:34:22.664 --> 01:34:24.624
I kept in touch with those guys
over the years,

01:34:24.708 --> 01:34:28.295
and I found out that Yeah- Yeah's parents
shipped him off to military school.

01:34:28.378 --> 01:34:32.257
After the army, he became one of the
pioneering developers of bungee jumping.

01:34:32.382 --> 01:34:34.217
Of course, we all know why.

01:34:34.342 --> 01:34:37.512
Bertram, well-- Bertram got
really into the '60s,

01:34:37.595 --> 01:34:39.639
and no one ever saw him again.

01:34:39.723 --> 01:34:43.643
Timmy and Tommy became
an architect and a contractor.

01:34:43.727 --> 01:34:46.062
They started out small,
designing playground equipment...

01:34:46.146 --> 01:34:48.273
and prefabricated tree houses.

01:34:48.398 --> 01:34:50.275
But they became
multimillionaires...

01:34:50.400 --> 01:34:54.237
when they invented
mini-malls.

01:34:54.321 --> 01:34:56.823
Squints grew up and married
Wendy Peffercorn.

01:34:56.906 --> 01:34:58.908
They have nine kids.

01:34:59.034 --> 01:35:02.704
They bought Vincent's Drugstore,
and they still own it to this day.

01:35:02.787 --> 01:35:05.540
Hamilton Porter became
a professional wrestler.

01:35:05.623 --> 01:35:07.876
You know him
as The Great Hambino.

01:35:07.959 --> 01:35:12.672
DeNunez played triple-A ball,
but he never got to the majors.

01:35:12.756 --> 01:35:15.550
He owns his own business now,
and he coaches a little league team...

01:35:15.634 --> 01:35:19.220
that his sons play on
called the Heaters.

01:35:19.304 --> 01:35:22.766
Hercules lived
to be 199 years old--

01:35:22.891 --> 01:35:24.768
uh, in doggy years.

01:35:24.893 --> 01:35:27.771
I was the last one
to move away.

01:35:27.896 --> 01:35:31.066
But when I did,
the sandlot was still there.

01:35:31.191 --> 01:35:35.028
After Benny pickled The Beast,
his reputation spread all over town.

01:35:35.111 --> 01:35:38.698
From then on, he was known as
Benny "The Jet" Rodriguez.

01:35:38.782 --> 01:35:42.369
And the nickname stuck with him
for the rest of his life.

01:35:42.452 --> 01:35:45.038
Now pinch running
for the Los Angeles Dodgers,

01:35:45.121 --> 01:35:48.958
Benny "The Jet" Rodriguez!

01:35:50.210 --> 01:35:53.463
It is the clutch situation
of the season.

01:35:53.588 --> 01:35:56.299
They say The Jet's lost
a step or two,

01:35:56.424 --> 01:36:00.136
but I wouldn't be surprised
to see some fireworks here.

01:36:02.430 --> 01:36:06.434
The Jet's got
a suicide lead and--

01:36:06.518 --> 01:36:09.312
And there he goes! He's stealing home!
I don't believe it!

01:36:09.396 --> 01:36:12.315
He's stealing home!

01:36:12.399 --> 01:36:15.819
He's stealing home,
and they don't see him! The pitch!

01:36:22.993 --> 01:36:25.912
He's hit the dirt!
He's safe! Safe!

01:36:25.996 --> 01:36:29.040
Oh, my God!

01:36:31.042 --> 01:36:33.253
Safe! Safe! Safe!

01:36:33.336 --> 01:36:37.674
I don't believe it! The Jet
stole home! The Jet stole home!

